Former Public Investment Corporation CEO, Dan Matjila, resigned from the PIC in November 2018. • Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Former Public Investment Corporation CEO, Dan Matjila, is back at the PIC Commission of Inquiry. He'll be back in the hot seat for the 10th day today. On Tuesday, he told the inquiry that under his leadership, the asset manager was very successful. He was responding to allegations made against him by previous witnesses. Matjila resigned from the PIC in November 2018.